OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
Another Bangladesh Wicket falls inside the powerplay! Shardul Thakur bowling to Anamul Haque, short of good length ball, pitching outside off stump, Anamul Haque once again tries to repeat the feat, looking to pull it across. This time gets a top edge as the ball hits high on the bat. Goes up a long way in the air for KL Rahul to settle under it and complete the formality. WICKET Anamul Haque c K L Rahul b Shardul Thakur (Bangladesh 28 Runs for 3 wickets)

A well made and steady half-century by @ShubmanGill ????

His 9th in ODIs.

Live - https://t.co/Qi56Y95GFN… #INDvBAN pic.twitter.com/79UjVkF14s

— BCCI (@BCCI) September 15, 2023

What a way to get to a half-century! Mahedi Hasan bowling to Shubman Gill, full length ball, pitching outside off stump, Shubman Gill steps down the track and flicks it towards deep mid-wicket to send it sailing over the ropes. No half-measures there from Shubman Gill! Brings up his 9th fifty in One dayers.

OverHistory.CommentStrikers: Mahedi Hasan TO Shubman Gill

OverHistory.UPDCommentry: WICKET! Mahedi Hasan bowling to Shubman Gill, full length ball, pitching outside off stump, Shubman Gill looking to repeat the feat this time going down the ground but fails to get the desired timing. Mistimes the lofted drive towards long-off where Hridoy takes a well-judged running catch! The bowler has the last laugh! An excellent innings from Shubman Gill comes to an end! WICKET Shubman Gill c Md Towhid Hridoy b Mahedi Hasan (India 209 Runs for 7 wickets)

OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
#TeamIndia put up a solid fight as the things went right down to the wire but it was Bangladesh who won the match.

Scorecard ?? https://t.co/OHhiRDZM6W#AsiaCup2023 | #INDvBAN pic.twitter.com/qy6Z4fbmiC

— BCCI (@BCCI) September 15, 2023

WICKET! Tanzim Hasan Sakib bowling to Mohammad Shami, yorker ball, pitching on off stump, Mohammad Shami deftly nudges the ball down to the fine leg region. The batsmen, in a desperate bid for a second run, push the boundaries of their speed. It's a high-pressure moment, with no room for hesitation, as the throw from the fielder arrives like a bullet right beside the stumps at the striker's end. Litton whips the bails off with Shami not even in the frame. Mohammad Shami run out Tanzid Hasan (India 259 Runs for 10 wickets)
